overview: >-
  The user initiated a request to enhance a sleep questionnaire application by
  integrating a database for response storage and developing an admin dashboard
  for data access. The core intent was to fulfill the requirements of a provided
  Statement of Work, which included data capture, simple retrieval (CSV
  download), and a client-facing dashboard.

  The approach involved a comprehensive evaluation of the existing codebase to
  identify gaps. Key decisions included using NeonDB (PostgreSQL) with Prisma
  for database management, implementing a simple password-based authentication
  system for the dashboard, and updating the questionnaire's demographic fields
  to align with the SOW while retaining existing relevant data.

  The outcome is a detailed implementation plan covering database schema design,
  API route development for saving and retrieving responses, creation of
  authentication middleware, and the development of an admin login and dashboard
  interface. The implementation has begun with the update of the demographics
  section in the application's types, validations, and UI components.
